**user**:
> In javascript/jquery, how can I watch a text area and if the user clears that, then I also want to clear a hidden variable?
**assistant**:
> To achieve this in JavaScript/jQuery, you can attach an event listener to the textarea that listens for input events. When the input event is triggered, you can check if the content of the textarea is empty. If it is, you can then clear the hidden variable. Here's a simple example:
> 
> ```html
> <textarea id="myTextarea"></textarea>
> <input type="hidden" id="myHiddenVariable" value="some value">
> 
> <script src="https://code.jquery.com/jquery-3.6.0.min.js"></script>
> <script>
> $(document).ready(function() {
>     $('#myTextarea').on('input', function() {
>         if ($(this).val() === '') {
>             $('#myHiddenVariable').val('');
>             console.log('Textarea cleared, hidden variable also cleared.');
>         }
>     });
> });
> </script>
> ```
> 
> In this example:
> 
> 1. A `textarea` with the id `myTextarea` is watched for changes.
> 2. When the content of the textarea changes, the `input` event is triggered.
> 3. Inside the event handler, we check if the textarea's value is an empty string.
> 4. If it is empty, we clear the value of the hidden input with the id `myHiddenVariable`.
> 
> This setup will ensure that whenever the user clears the textarea, the hidden variable is also cleared.
